Bringing wine to your next party, but unsure which kind is best or how many? Well, take these pointers from @sommvivant🍷 
1. Stock up on sparkling wine because it goes well with just about any food and any celebration 
2. Invited to a dinner party? Go for low tannin wines like Pinot Noir
3. Rosé is also a great versatile, food-pairing wine
4. Searching for a specific location on the bottle & sustainability certification will promise you a higher-quality wine 
5. And bring 2 bottles. One for the party host to drink now and one to drink later 😉 @nbccalive 
.
. 
#wine #holidays #holidaywine #wineetiquette #nbcalive #californialive #winesommelier

How we spent the last day of 2023 🥰 Instead of driving 5 hours down to LA, we decided to sit back & relax on a 12 hour train ride. Booked a private room, enjoyed complimentary meals, watched a movie, soaked in the scenic views, played cards, talked, set our intentions for 2024 and just embraced this one-on-one time together that we rarely get nowadays taking care of our little one. It was a nice way to wind down another crazy year. Excited to let God lead us into this new year, because He already set it off right with that Michigan win 😜 (stay tuned for the next reel)
.
.
